</fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {A}]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-0010.xml" title="Path object" addr="//erct/erct-0010" type="local">path object</fr:link>. Any <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-0031.xml" title="Left cleaving of a family of path objects" addr="//erct/erct-0031" type="local">left-cloven family of path objects</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {B}\colon  
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert \mathcal {A}\right \rvert \mathclose {}
\to  \mathsf {PathObj}]]></fr:tex> gives rise to a canonical <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-0012.xml" title="Displayed path object" addr="//erct/erct-0012" type="local">displayed path object</fr:link> over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {A}]]></fr:tex> in which:</fr:p><fr:ol><fr:li>for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p\colon  x\approx _{\mathcal {A}} y]]></fr:tex>, we define <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b\approx _{\mathcal {B}}^{p} b']]></fr:tex> to be <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p_*b \approx _{\mathcal {B} y} b']]></fr:tex>;</fr:li>
 <fr:li>for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x:
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert \mathcal {A}\right \rvert \mathclose {}
]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b:
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert \mathcal {B} x\right \rvert \mathclose {}
]]></fr:tex>, the identity element <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {rx}_{\mathcal {B}}{x}\colon  b \approx _{\mathcal {B}}^{\mathsf {rx}_{\mathcal {A}}{x}}b]]></fr:tex> is given by the component <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Phi _{\mathcal {B}} xb\colon  
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen \mathsf {rx}_{\mathcal {A}}{x}\right \rparen \mathclose {}
_*b\approx _{\mathcal {B} x}{b}]]></fr:tex> of the unit law of the given right cleaving of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {B}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li></fr:ol>
 
   
